can we use just smth like this for a web api call and respond before it finishes?

Action<cancellationtoken> workItem = PostToRemoteService;  
 HostingEnvironment.QueueBackgroundWorkItem(workItem);

I'm wondering why isn't there a return from Run, returning the Task?

public Task Run(Action operation)  
 {  
 var task = Task.Run(operation);  
 Register(task);  
 return task;  
 }
